-- Bats Agrees to Merge With U.S. Exchange Competitor Direct Edge
-- B y   L y n n   T h o m a s s o n
-- 2013-08-26T13:10:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-26/bats-agrees-to-merge-with-u-s-exchange-competitor-direct-edge.html
Bats Global Markets Inc. and Direct
Edge LLC said they agreed to merge in a transaction that will
create the second-largest U.S. stock exchange operator.  Financial terms of the agreement will not be disclosed, the
companies said in a press release today. If approved by
regulators, the deal is expected to close in the first half of
2014, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
